User: Why is the sky blue?
Think: The user is asking about the physics of the atmosphere. Sunlight is scattered by air molecules. Blue light scatters more than other colors because it travels in shorter, smaller waves.
Assistant: It is due to Rayleigh scattering. The atmosphere scatters blue light more than other colors because it travels in shorter, smaller waves.

